snippet.textDisplay: I'm not a pilot aside from the virtual world of aviation video games, but I have to seriously ask why, according to repots, did the civil authorities give Mr. Bryant's helicopter clearance to fly in such dangerous weather conditions. Reports are saying that even Police helicopter pilots refused to fly that day because of the weather conditions. This brings up the question of WHO decided to risk the flight. Who or what prompted civil authorities to give the helicopter "special" clearance to fly. It's possible that the helicopter pilot voiced his concerns about the flight, but was "overruled by another's decision to risk the flight so that Mr. Bryant could make his appointment at the sports center. Another possibility is that the pilot, wanting to impress his VIP passengers, took it upon himself to request special clearance to attempt the flight. I hope that the investigation will reveal the truth no matter what form it takes.
